"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-04-19-sports-federations-condemn-olympic-prize-money-athletics\", \"noun_phrases\": [{\"sentence\": \"LAUSANNE, Switzerland (AFP) - An organisation of Olympic sports federations on Friday said the decision by World Athletics to award prize money to gold medallists in its events \\\"undermines the values of Olympism\\\".\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 213, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 10, \"end\": 21, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"score\": 0.9995614184690812, \"rank\": 0.00034439384150988735, \"text\": \"Switzerland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Switzerland\"}, {\"begin\": 107, \"end\": 122, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.74466104786243e-13, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"LAUSANNE\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 8}, {\"ngram\": \"(AFP\", \"from\": 22, \"to\": 26}, {\"ngram\": \"An organisation\", \"from\": 30, \"to\": 45}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic sports federations\", \"from\": 49, \"to\": 75}, {\"ngram\": \"Friday\", \"from\": 79, \"to\": 85}, {\"ngram\": \"the decision\", \"from\": 91, \"to\": 103}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 132, \"to\": 143}, {\"ngram\": \"gold medallists\", \"from\": 147, \"to\": 162}, {\"ngram\": \"its events\", \"from\": 166, \"to\": 176}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 189, \"to\": 199}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympism\", \"from\": 203, \"to\": 211}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Association of Summer Olympic International Federations (ASOIF) released a statement which made clear how unhappy it was at the announcement by World Athletics president Sebastian Coe that track and field gold medallists at the Paris Games will receive US$50,000 (47,000 euros).\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 497, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 363, \"end\": 378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.74466104786243e-13, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}, {\"begin\": 389, \"end\": 402, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sebastian Coe\", \"types\": [\"Q82955\", \"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sebastian_Coe\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Association\", \"from\": 215, \"to\": 230}, {\"ngram\": \"Summer Olympic International Federations\", \"from\": 234, \"to\": 274}, {\"ngram\": \"ASOIF\", \"from\": 276, \"to\": 281}, {\"ngram\": \"a statement\", \"from\": 292, \"to\": 303}, {\"ngram\": \"the announcement\", \"from\": 343, \"to\": 359}, {\"ngram\": \"that track and field gold medallists\", \"from\": 403, \"to\": 439}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris Games\", \"from\": 443, \"to\": 458}, {\"ngram\": \"US$50,000 (47,000 euros\", \"from\": 472, \"to\": 495}]}, {\"sentence\": \"World Athletics' move, announced last week, was for a first for a federation at an Olympics.\", \"from\": 499, \"to\": 591, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 499, \"end\": 514, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"score\": 0.9999999999990905, \"rank\": 8.74466104786243e-13, \"text\": \"World Athletics\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/World_Athletics\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a federation\", \"from\": 563, \"to\": 575}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympics\", \"from\": 579, \"to\": 590}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It said it would extend prize money to all medallists in Los Angeles in four years' time.\", \"from\": 592, \"to\": 681, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 649, \"end\": 660, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"score\": 0.999999417660489, \"rank\": 4.082406077453213e-07, \"text\": \"Los Angeles\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Los_Angeles\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 616, \"to\": 627}, {\"ngram\": \"all medallists\", \"from\": 631, \"to\": 645}, {\"ngram\": \"four years' time\", \"from\": 664, \"to\": 680}]}, {\"sentence\": \"ASOIF, which has 30 full members and two associate members, said: \\\"This move undermines the values of Olympism and the uniqueness of the Games.\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"ASOIF\", \"from\": 683, \"to\": 688}, {\"ngram\": \"30 full members\", \"from\": 700, \"to\": 715}, {\"ngram\": \"two associate members\", \"from\": 720, \"to\": 741}, {\"ngram\": \"This move\", \"from\": 750, \"to\": 759}, {\"ngram\": \"the values\", \"from\": 771, \"to\": 781}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympism\", \"from\": 785, \"to\": 793}, {\"ngram\": \"the uniqueness\", \"from\": 798, \"to\": 812}, {\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 816, \"to\": 825}]}, {\"sentence\": \"One cannot and should not put a price on an Olympic gold medal.\\\"\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 891, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"One\", \"from\": 827, \"to\": 830}, {\"ngram\": \"a price\", \"from\": 857, \"to\": 864}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic gold medal\", \"from\": 868, \"to\": 889}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"This disregards the less privileged athletes lower down the final standings.\\\"\", \"from\": 893, \"to\": 971, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the less privileged athletes\", \"from\": 910, \"to\": 938}, {\"ngram\": \"the final standings\", \"from\": 950, \"to\": 969}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It said other Olympic sports cannot afford to offer prize money.\", \"from\": 973, \"to\": 1037, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"other Olympic sports\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1001}, {\"ngram\": \"prize money\", \"from\": 1025, \"to\": 1036}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Not all sports could or should replicate this move, even if they wanted to,\\\" said ASOIF.\", \"from\": 1039, \"to\": 1128, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Not all sports\", \"from\": 1040, \"to\": 1054}, {\"ngram\": \"this move\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1090}, {\"ngram\": \"ASOIF\", \"from\": 1122, \"to\": 1127}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organisation added that it accepted schemes by National Olympic Committees and governments to \\\"reward athletes for outstanding performances\\u2026for purposes of national pride and \\u2026consistently across all the sports at the Olympic Games.\\\"\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1367, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1181, \"end\": 1208, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 0.9999999051140139, \"rank\": 9.488594221066127e-08, \"text\": \"National Olympic Committees\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The organisation\", \"from\": 1130, \"to\": 1146}, {\"ngram\": \"schemes\", \"from\": 1170, \"to\": 1177}, {\"ngram\": \"governments\", \"from\": 1213, \"to\": 1224}, {\"ngram\": \"athletes\", \"from\": 1236, \"to\": 1244}, {\"ngram\": \"outstanding performances\", \"from\": 1249, \"to\": 1273}, {\"ngram\": \"purposes\", \"from\": 1278, \"to\": 1286}, {\"ngram\": \"national pride\", \"from\": 1290, \"to\": 1304}, {\"ngram\": \"all the sports\", \"from\": 1330, \"to\": 1344}, {\"ngram\": \"the Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1365}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It also said that there had been a consensus that, where sports had a surplus, Olympic revenue should \\\"be invested as a priority into development and integrity\\\".\", \"from\": 1369, \"to\": 1530, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a consensus\", \"from\": 1402, \"to\": 1413}, {\"ngram\": \"sports\", \"from\": 1426, \"to\": 1432}, {\"ngram\": \"a surplus\", \"from\": 1437, \"to\": 1446}, {\"ngram\": \"Olympic revenue\", \"from\": 1448, \"to\": 1463}, {\"ngram\": \"a priority\", \"from\": 1487, \"to\": 1497}, {\"ngram\": \"development\", \"from\": 1503, \"to\": 1514}, {\"ngram\": \"integrity\", \"from\": 1519, \"to\": 1528}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The organisation was also unhappy that Coe had announced the move without warning to its fellow federations, although it had informed the International Olympic Committee on the day of the announcement.\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1733, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1670, \"end\": 1701, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"International Olympic Committee\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/International_Olympic_Committee\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The organisation\", \"from\": 1532, \"to\": 1548}, {\"ngram\": \"Coe\", \"from\": 1571, \"to\": 1574}, {\"ngram\": \"the move\", \"from\": 1589, \"to\": 1597}, {\"ngram\": \"its fellow federations\", \"from\": 1617, \"to\": 1639}, {\"ngram\": \"the day\", \"from\": 1705, \"to\": 1712}, {\"ngram\": \"the announcement\", \"from\": 1716, \"to\": 1732}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"ASOIF was neither informed nor consulted in advance of the announcement, which was made one day after the ASOIF General Assembly,\\\" it said, adding \\\"it is important and fair to discuss the matter at stake with the other federations in advance\\\".\", \"from\": 1735, \"to\": 1979, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1848, \"end\": 1864, \"tit